  <heading>SMAXV</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Signed maximum reduction to scalar</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction performs a signed maximum horizontally across all lanes of a vector, and places the result in the
SIMD&amp;FP scalar destination register.
 Inactive elements in the source vector are treated as the minimum signed integer for the element size.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
